{"cursor":"2268","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Alberto Berdini da Sarteano' (1385 - 15 August 1450) was a 15th-century\nFranciscan friar, and an apostolic delegate for Ethiopia, India, Egypt and\nJerusalem.\n\nSarteano was born in Sarteano. In 1439 he was sent by Pope Eugenius IV to\ndeliver a letter to the Christians Copts so that they could participate to the\nCouncil of Florence and thus take part to the ongoing efforts to unite all\nChristian churches. Alberto Berdini returned to Italy on 26 August 1441, with\nfour Ethiopians and Copts, although eventually the efforts at reunion proved fruitless. [http://books.google.com/books?id=Dg-\n8ZOeBqcYC&pg=PA81&dq=Coucil+Florence+Ethiopians&as_brr=3&hl=en#PPA81,M1 Quinn\nThe European Outthrust and Encounter p.81] [http://books.google.com/b-\nooks?id=YLmhCHtydKMC&pg=PA128&dq=Coucil+Florence+Ethiopians&as_brr=3&hl=en#PPA1-\n28,M1 Trexler The journey of the Magi p.128]\n\nFrom 1442 to 1443, he became Vicar general of the Order of Friars Minor (he was\ninterim Minister General, i.e. head of the entire order before the nomination of\na new Minister General following the death of the previous one). [http://bo-\noks.google.com/books?id=KJOXBGHvB6MC&pg=PR10&dq=Sarteano+Vicar+General&as_brr=3-\n&hl=en Robson The Franciscans in the Middle Ages, p.10] He died in Milan,\naged about 65.\n","linknr":111,"url":"Alberto_Berdini_de_Sarteano","recorded":1375077750,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Alberto_da_Sarteano&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Alberto_da_Sarteano&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Alberto_da_Sarteano","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPri